  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into batons</p><p>Add the <strong>carrot batons </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with a generous splash of <strong>cold water </strong>and a small knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Scrunch the foil around them to form a tightly sealed parcel and add to a baking tray (or two!)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707212117329-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707212117329-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707212117329-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707212117329-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1707212117329-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the tray[s] in the oven and cook for an initial 15 min</p><p>Meanwhile, peel your <strong>potatoes </strong>and chop them in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a large heat-proof bowl covered with<strong> cling film</strong></p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 5-8 min or until slightly tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
